  "prompt": "What is a vitamin?",
  "response": "Vitamins are organic compounds that are essential in small amounts for various metabolic processes in the body. They play crucial roles in maintaining health and well-being. Vitamins are classified into two main categories: \n\n1. **Water-soluble Vitamins**: These include the B-complex vitamins (such as B1, B2, B3, B5, B6, B7, B9, and B12) and vitamin C. They dissolve in water and are not stored in the body, which means they need to be consumed regularly through diet.\n\n2. **Fat-soluble Vitamins**: These include vitamins A, D, E, and K. They are soluble in fats and can be stored in the body\u2019s fatty tissues and liver for later use.\n\nVitamins are obtained from various food sources, and each vitamin has specific functions within the body, including roles in immune function, energy production, blood clotting, and the maintenance of healthy skin and eyesight. A deficiency in any of these vitamins can lead to health issues.",
